The paper deals with algorithms for approximating matrix multiplication, which is a fundamental problem in computer science and has applications in many areas such as machine learning, signal processing, and scientific computing. The paper uses tools from high-dimensional geometry, concentration of measure, and matrix analysis, which are typically studied in subfields such as data structures (cs.DS), information theory (cs.IT), machine learning (cs.LG), numerical analysis (cs.NA), and systems and control (cs.SY).
